I need a bit of simple advice. On your example layout, the numbers are centered perfectly inside it’s container. I applied three css rules to get that alignment, witch are.
1) text-align: center;
2) top: 50%;
3) transform: translateY(-50%);

And in doing so my css grid collapsed only showing the third row.
So how do I align my text properly using css grid without it collapsing my grid.

One thing to note: I am using two external stylesheets, one for styling and the other for css grid

Thanks!

replies.text:
You can use flex-box in the items:
align-items: center;
display: flex;
justify-content: center;

Use floats, it's a very bad idea, you can combine display grid and display flex for almost everything.

For your HEADER example you can do this:
header{
   align-items: center;
   display: flex;
   justify-content: space-between;
}

The align item it's gonna put your divs in the middle of a parent div.
The display flex its gonna give you the same result as float without his troubles, like the ::after issues.
And the justify content it's gonna separate the content of the div (logo and menu)

You can read this: https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/

